The paper discusses the challenge of estimating gradients through stochastic neurons in deep learning models, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of optimization and learning (cs.LG). The paper also explores different approaches to address this problem, including the use of stochastic binary neurons, which is a topic related to neural networks (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the potential applications of these approaches in image processing (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY).
